original: Larsson, Lars, läroverksadjunkt, Norrköping, f. 15/12/92 i Karlstad av trävaruhandl. Halvar L. o. Elin Knud-sen. G. 20 m. Svea Llellman. Barn: Lars-Olov f. 26. — Stud:ex. i Karlstad II, fil. mag. i Upps. 17, provår där 21-22. Vik. adj. i Hudiksvall 20-21, e. o. lektor i Söderhamn 22-28, adj. i Falköp. 28, adj. i tyska o. franska v. Norrköp. h. a. 1. sed. 33. Språkstud. i Frankr. 12, 35, 36 o. 38, Engl. 14, 21, 23 o. 34, Tyskl. 27.
translated: Larsson, Lars, student teacher, Norrköping, born on December 15, 1892 in Karlstad to timber merchant Halvar L. and Elin Knudsen. Married in 1920 to Svea Llellman. Children: Lars-Olov, born in 1926. Completed high school in Karlstad in 1911, B.A. in Uppsala in 1917, and spent a trial year there in 1921-1922. Temporary teacher in Hudiksvall from 1920-1921, substitute lecturer in Söderhamn from 1922-1928. Became an adjunct teacher in Falköping in 1928, and in German and French at Norrköping since 1933. Language studies in France in 1912, 1935, 1936, and 1938, English in 1914, 1921, 1923, and 1934, and German in 1927.
